## ğŸ”¥ Quick Start  

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Import the package  
```python
import pandas as pd
import fireviz as fv
```

### 2ï¸âƒ£ Load your dataset  
```python
df = pd.read_csv("data.csv")
```

### 3ï¸âƒ£ Generate Quick Visualizations  

#### ğŸ“Œ Scatter Plot  
```python
fv.plot(df, x="column1", y="column2", kind="scatter")
```

#### ğŸ“Œ Histogram  
```python
fv.plot(df["column1"], kind="hist", bins=20)
```

#### ğŸ“Œ Correlation Heatmap  
```python
fv.plot(df, kind="heatmap")
```

#### ğŸ“Œ Treemap  
```python
fv.plot(df, x="category_column", y="value_column", kind="treemap")
```

---

## ğŸ” Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)  

The **`explore()`** function automatically generates visual summaries of your dataset.  
```python
fv.explore(df)
```
This will:  
âœ… Print **dataset info, missing values, and statistics**  
âœ… Plot **histograms** for numeric columns  
âœ… Plot **count plots** for categorical columns  
âœ… Generate a **correlation heatmap**  

